der that includes `Annotation`, `Distance to TSS` (renamed\n`Distance.to.TSS` by R) and `Nearest PromoterID`.\n\nProduce:\n  - `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv`: a wide table (one row per sample) with the\n    count of peaks per first-token feature (exon, Intergenic, intron, promoter-TSS,\n    TTS, ...).\n  - `output/homer_annot.pdf`: a multi-page PDF containing (1) a stacked feature-\n    proportion barplot, (2) a stacked distance-bin barplot (<2kb/<5kb/<10kb/>10kb\n    based on each unique gene's closest peak) and (3) a log10 violin plot of the\n    `Distance.to.TSS` distribution per sample.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/homer_annot.pdf` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: homer_annot.pdf, homer_annot_summary.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n", "name": "read_text_file", "tool_call_id": "call_zlFoAX49VAfW99fmDPPxX1Ja"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_LJNhfbrg2wVpwNiB7MyTvRvj", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. **Read Input Files**: Load `sampleA_anno.txt`, `sampleB_anno.txt`, `sampleC_anno.txt` from the `input/` directory.\\n2. **Data Transformation**:\\n   - Extract the first token from the `Annotation` column for each file.\\n   - Count occurrences of each feature type (e.g., exon, Intergenic, intron, etc.).\\n   - Create a summary table with counts per feature type for each sample.\\n3. **Output Summary Table**:\\n   - Write the summary table to `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv`.\\n4. **Plotting**:\\n   - Create a stacked barplot of feature proportions for each sample.\\n   - Create a stacked barplot of distance bins (<2kb, <5kb, <10kb, >10kb) based on the closest peak to each unique gene.\\n   - Create a log10 violin plot of the `Distance.to.TSS` distribution for each sample.\\n5. **Output PDF**:\\n   - Save the plots in a multi-page PDF `output/homer_annot.pdf`.\\n6. **Validation**:\\n   - Ensure `output/homer_annot.pdf` and `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv` are created.\\n7. **Completion**:\\n   - Call `submit_done(success=true)` once outputs are verified.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (1041 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_LJNhfbrg2wVpwNiB7MyTvRvj"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_gKtOFfAMG8Lvo0GTA5DWK0cE", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"# Load necessary libraries\\nlibrary(ggplot2)\\nlibrary(dplyr)\\nlibrary(tidyr)\\nlibrary(ggpubr)\\n\\n# Define input files\\ninput_files <- list('sampleA' = 'input/sampleA_anno.txt',\\n                    'sampleB' = 'input/sampleB_anno.txt',\\n                    'sampleC' = 'input/sampleC_anno.txt')\\n\\n# Initialize list to store data\\ndata_list <- list()\\n\\n# Read and process each file\\nfor (sample in names(input_files)) {\\n  # Read the data\\n  data <- read.delim(input_files[[sample]], header = TRUE, sep = '\\\\t')\\n  \\n  # Extract first token from Annotation\\n  data$Feature <- sapply(strsplit(as.character(data$Annotation), ' '), `[`, 1)\\n  \\n  # Count occurrences of each feature type\\n  feature_counts <- data %>%\\n    group_by(Feature) %>%\\n    summarise(Count = n())\\n  \\n  # Store in list\\n  data_list[[sample]] <- feature_counts\\n}\\n\\n# Combine data into a wide format\\nsummary_table <- bind_rows(data_list, .id = 'Sample') %>%\\n  pivot_wider(names_from = Feature, values_from = Count, values_fill = 0)\\n\\n# Write summary table to file\\nwrite.table(summary_table, 'output/homer_annot_summary.tsv', sep = '\\\\t', row.names = FALSE)\\n\\n# Create plots\\npdf('output/homer_annot.pdf')\\n\\n# Plot 1: Stacked feature-proportion barplot\\nfeature_plot <- ggplot(summary_table, aes(x = Sample)) +\\n  geom_bar(aes(y = exon, fill = 'exon'), stat = 'identity') +\\n  geom_bar(aes(y = Intergenic, fill = 'Intergenic'), stat = 'identity') +\\n  geom_bar(aes(y = intron, fill = 'intron'), stat = 'identity') +\\n  geom_bar(aes(y = `promoter-TSS`, fill = 'promoter-TSS'), stat = 'identity') +\\n  geom_bar(aes(y = TTS, fill = 'TTS'), stat = 'identity') +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  labs(title = 'Feature Proportion per Sample', y = 'Count', fill = 'Feature')\\n\\nprint(feature_plot)\\n\\n# Plot 2: Stacked distance-bin barplot\\n# Create distance bins\\nfor (sample in names(input_files)) {\\n  data <- read.delim(input_files[[sample]], header = TRUE, sep = '\\\\t')\\n  data$DistanceBin <- cut(abs(data$Distance.to.TSS), breaks = c(-Inf, 2000, 5000, 10000, Inf),\\n                          labels = c('<2kb', '<5kb', '<10kb', '>10kb'))\\n  distance_counts <- data %>%\\n    group_by(DistanceBin) %>%\\n    summarise(Count = n())\\n  distance_counts$Sample <- sample\\n  data_list[[sample]] <- distance_counts\\n}\\n\\ndistance_table <- bind_rows(data_list)\\n\\ndistance_plot <- ggplot(distance_table, aes(x = Sample, y = Count, fill = DistanceBin)) +\\n  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', position = 'stack') +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  labs(title = 'Distance to TSS Bins per Sample', y = 'Count', fill = 'Distance Bin')\\n\\nprint(distance_plot)\\n\\n# Plot 3: Log10 violin plot of Distance.to.TSS\\nviolin_plot <- ggplot(bind_rows(data_list, .id = 'Sample'), aes(x = Sample, y = log10(abs(Distance.to.TSS)))) +\\n  geom_violin() +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  labs(title = 'Log10 Distance to TSS Distribution', y = 'Log10 Distance to TSS')\\n\\nprint(violin_plot)\\n\\ndev.off()\\n\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation": [{"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (1041 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_LJNhfbrg2wVpwNiB7MyTvRvj"}], "next_observation": [{"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\n\nAttaching package: \u2018dplyr\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u201