er that includes `Annotation`, `Distance to TSS` (renamed\n`Distance.to.TSS` by R) and `Nearest PromoterID`.\n\nProduce:\n  - `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv`: a wide table (one row per sample) with the\n    count of peaks per first-token feature (exon, Intergenic, intron, promoter-TSS,\n    TTS, ...).\n  - `output/homer_annot.pdf`: a multi-page PDF containing (1) a stacked feature-\n    proportion barplot, (2) a stacked distance-bin barplot (<2kb/<5kb/<10kb/>10kb\n    based on each unique gene's closest peak) and (3) a log10 violin plot of the\n    `Distance.to.TSS` distribution per sample.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/homer_annot.pdf` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: homer_annot.pdf, homer_annot_summary.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_anno.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_anno.txt\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_anno.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_anno.txt\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_anno.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_anno.txt\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/homer_annot.pdf` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_Me6oaiQscUZCfpIrbxodKqLE", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "list_workdir"}}, {"id": "call_zlFoAX49VAfW99fmDPPxX1Ja", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_anno.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_anno.txt\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_anno.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_anno.txt\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_anno.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_anno.txt\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}", "name": "list_workdir", "tool_call_id": "call_Me6oaiQscUZCfpIrbxodKqLE"}, {"role": "tool", "content": "# Real R-task: chipseq_plot_homer_annot\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `snakemake-workflows-chipseq` (family: `chipseq`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given three HOMER `annotatePeaks.pl` outputs under `input/`:\n`sampleA_anno.txt`, `sampleB_anno.txt`, `sampleC_anno.txt`. Each file is tab-\nseparated with a header that includes `Annotation`, `Distance to TSS` (renamed\n`Distance.to.TSS` by R) and `Nearest PromoterID`.\n\nProduce:\n  - `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv`: a wide table (one row per sample) with the\n    count of peaks per first-token feature (exon, Intergenic, intron, promoter-TSS,\n    TTS, ...).\n  - `output/homer_annot.pdf`: a multi-page PDF containing (1) a stacked feature-\n    proportion barplot, (2) a stacked distance-bin barplot (<2kb/<5kb/<10kb/>10kb\n    based on each unique gene's closest peak) and (3) a log10 violin plot of the\n    `Distance.to.TSS` distribution per sample.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/homer_annot.pdf` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: homer_annot.pdf, homer_annot_summary.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n", "name": "read_text_file", "tool_call_id": "call_zlFoAX49VAfW99fmDPPxX1Ja"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_LJNhfbrg2wVpwNiB7MyTvRvj", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. **Read Input Files**: Load `sampleA_anno.txt`, `sampleB_anno.txt`, `sampleC_anno.txt` from the `input/` directory.\\n2. **Data Transformation**:\\n   - Extract the first token from the `Annotation` column for each file.\\n   - Count occurrences of each feature type (e.g., exon, Intergenic, intron, etc.).\\n   - Create a summary table with counts per feature type for each sample.\\n3. **Output Summary Table**:\\n   - Write the summary table to `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv`.\\n4. **Plotting**:\\n   - Create a stacked barplot of feature proportions for each sample.\\n   - Create a stacked barplot of distance bins (<2kb, <5kb, <10kb, >10kb) based on the closest peak to each unique gene.\\n   - Create a log10 violin plot of the `Distance.to.TSS` distribution for each sample.\\n5. **Output PDF**:\\n   - Save the plots in a multi-page PDF `output/homer_annot.pdf`.\\n6. **Validation**:\\n   - Ensure `output/homer_annot.pdf` and `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv` are created.\\n7. **Completion**:\\n   - Call `submit_done(success=true)` once outputs are verified.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (1041 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_LJNhfbrg2wVpwNiB7MyTvRvj"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_gKtOFfAMG8Lvo0GTA5DWK0cE", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"# Load necessary libraries\\nlibrary(ggplot2)\\nlibrary(dplyr)\\nlibrary(tidyr)\\nlibrary(ggpubr)\\n\\n# Define input files\\ninput_files <- list('sampleA' = 'input/sampleA_anno.txt',\\n                    'sampleB' = 'input/sampleB_anno.txt',\\n                    'sampleC' = 'input/sampleC_anno.txt')\\n\\n# Initialize list to store data\\ndata_list <- list()\\n\\n# Read and process each file\\nfor (sample in names(input_files)) {\\n  # Read the data\\n  data <- read.delim(input_files[[sample]], header = TRUE, sep = '\\\\t')\\n  \\n  # Extract first token from Annotation\\n  data$Feature <- sapply(strsplit(as.character(data$Annotation), ' '), `[`, 1)\\n  \\n  # Count occurrences of each feature type\\n  feature_counts <- data %>%\\n    group_by(Feature) %>%\\n    summarise(Count = n())\\n  \\n  # Store in list\\n  data_list[[sample]] <- feature_counts\\n}\\n\\n# Combine data into a wide format\\nsummary_table <- bind_rows(data_list, .id = 'Sample') %>%\\n  pivot_wider(names_from = Feature, values_from = Count, values_fill = 0)\\n\\n# Write summary table to file\\nwrite.table(summary_table, 'output/homer_annot_summary.tsv', sep = '\\\\t', row.names = FALSE)\\n\\n# Create plots\\npdf('output/homer_annot.pdf')\\n\\n# Plot 1: Stacked feature-proportion barplot\\nfeature_plot <- ggplot(summary_table, aes(x = Sample)) +\\n  geom_bar(aes(y = exon, fill = 'exon'), stat = 'identity') +\\n  geom_bar(aes(y = Intergenic, fill = 'Intergenic'), stat = 'identity') +\\n  geom_bar(aes(y = intron, fill = 'intron'), stat = 'identity') +\\n  geom_bar(aes(y = `promoter-TSS`, fill = 'promoter-TSS'), stat = 'identity') +\\n  geom_bar(aes(y = TTS, fill = 'TTS'), stat = 'identity') +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  labs(title = 'Feature Proportion per Sample', y = 'Count', fill = 'Feature')\\n\\nprint(feature_plot)\\n\\n# Plot 2: Stacked distance-bin barplot\\n# Create distance bins\\nfor (sample in names(input_files)) {\\n  data <- read.delim(input_files[[sample]], header = TRUE, sep = '\\\\t')\\n  data$DistanceBin <- cut(abs(data$Distance.to.TSS), breaks = c(-Inf, 2000, 5000, 10000, Inf),\\n                          labels = c('<2kb', '<5kb', '<10kb', '>10kb'))\\n  distance_counts <- data %>%\\n    group_by(DistanceBin) %>%\\n    summarise(Count = n())\\n  distance_counts$Sample <- sample\\n  data_list[[sample]] <- distance_counts\\n}\\n\\ndistance_table <- bind_rows(data_list)\\n\\ndistance_plot <- ggplot(distance_table, aes(x = Sample, y = Count, fill = DistanceBin)) +\\n  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', position = 'stack') +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  labs(title = 'Distance to TSS Bins per Sample', y = 'Count', fill = 'Distance Bin')\\n\\nprint(distance_plot)\\n\\n# Plot 3: Log10 violin plot of Distance.to.TSS\\nviolin_plot <- ggplot(bind_rows(data_list, .id = 'Sample'), aes(x = Sample, y = log10(abs(Distance.to.TSS)))) +\\n  geom_violin() +\\n  theme_minimal() +\\n  labs(title = 'Log10 Distance to TSS Distribution', y = 'Log10 Distance to TSS')\\n\\nprint(violin_plot)\\n\\ndev.off()\\n\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\n\nAttaching package: \u2018dplyr\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    filter, lag\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    intersect, setdiff, setequal, union\n\nError in `geom_violin()`:\n! Problem while computing aesthetics.\n\u2139 Error occurred in the 1st layer.\nCaused by error:\n! object 'Distance.to.TSS' not found\nBacktrace:\n     \u2586\n  1. \u251c\u2500base::print(violin_plot)\n  2. \u251c\u2500ggplot2 (local) `print.ggplot2::ggplot`(violin_plot)\n  3. \u2502 \u251c\u2500ggplot2::ggplot_build(x)\n  4. \u2502 \u2514\u2500ggplot2 (local) `ggplot_build.ggplot2::ggplot`(x)\n  5. \u2502   \u2514\u2500ggplot2:::by_layer(...)\n  6. \u2502     \u251c\u2500rlang::try_fetch(...)\n  7. \u2502     \u2502 \u251c\u2500base::tryCatch(...)\n  8. \u2502     \u2502 \u2502 \u2514\u2500base (local) tryCatchList(expr, classes, parentenv, handlers)\n  9. \u2502     \u2502 \u2502   \u2514\u2500base (local) tryCatchOne(expr, names, parentenv, handlers[[1L]])\n 10. \u2502     \u2502 \u2502     \u2514\u2500base (local) doTryCatch(return(expr), name, parentenv, handler)\n 11. \u2502     \u2502 \u2514\u2500base::withCallingHandlers(...)\n 12. \u2502     \u2514\u2500ggplot2 (local) f(l = layers[[i]], d = data[[i]])\n 13. \u2502       \u2514\u2500l$compute_aesthetics(d, plot)\n 14. \u2502         \u2514\u2500ggplot2 (local) compute_aesthetics(..., self = self)\n 15. \u2502           \u2514\u2500ggplot